# {{lb|en|medicine}} An anesthetic (anesthetic substance) that causes loss of sensation only to the area to which it is applied.
#* '''1929''', [[w:Ernest Hemingway|Ernest Hemingway]], ''A Farewell to Arms'', chapter 15
#*: He used a '''local anaesthetic''' called something or other "snow," which froze the tissue and avoided pain until the probe, the scalpel or the forceps got below the frozen portion.

